  "id": "BIT-pillow-2026-59200",
  "summary": "Pillow: Decompression Bomb DoS via PdfParser.PdfStream.decode()",
  "details": "Pillow is a Python imaging library. From 5.1.0 until 12.3.0, PdfParser.PdfStream.decode() in PIL/PdfParser.py calls zlib.decompress() with bufsize set to the PDF stream Length field without bounding the decompressed output size, allowing a crafted FlateDecode PDF stream to exhaust memory from a small file. This issue is fixed in version 12.3.0.",
